        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="Seal of the Montreal Literary Club"><placeName>MONTREAL</placeName> LITERARY
                CLUB<lb/> NUNC LIBRIS VETERUM NUNC SOMNO ET INERTIBUS HORIS</p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Montreal</placeName>
                <date>13th August 5625</date>
            </p>
            <p>The <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">I should have written<lb/> you ere this, but it was long<lb/> before
                I could obtain a final reply<lb/> from the <persName>Rev Mr Hass</persName> who<lb/>
                has concluded now not to take<lb/> the volumes of sermons, as the<lb/> price he says
                is too high for him<lb/> and he was told he could get them<lb/> for two dollars.
                Entre nous, <persName>Mr<lb/> Hass</persName> is at present too much<lb/> engaged
                with manufacturing<lb/> vinegar, to cultivate pulpit eloquence<lb/> and as he has
                lost nearly all<lb/> his best members, there may</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>possibly exist another reason or<lb/> inducement less to invest. He<lb/> asked me
                when he saw me to<lb/> request you to discontinue<lb/> sending him the Occident
                because<lb/> “he did not order it.”</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I am very much obliged<lb/> to you for sending me the missing<lb/>
                numbers of the Occident. By<lb/> error however the number<lb/> 49 of vol 17 was sent
                me for<lb/> no 49 of vol eighteen which<lb/> latter number I want. Will<lb/> you
                please let me have it at<lb/> your convenience when my set<lb/> will be
                complete.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I hear that <persName>Mr<lb/> Samuel Benjamin</persName> is
                about<lb/> visiting <placeName>Canada</placeName>—will probably</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>be here in three weeks. I will<lb/> not fail to remind him of his<lb/> indebtedness
                to you.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I leave town with my<lb/> family tomorrow for a few
                weeks—<lb/>though I shall be here for <add>שבת</add>—and<lb/> having some
                preparations to make<lb/> must close this now. Hoping you<lb/> are enjoying good
                health and all<lb/> other pleasant things</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">I remain my dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">yours truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">
                <persName role="author">Abraham de Sola</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
